Initialized(uint8).details: Triggered when the contract has been initialized or reinitialized.

returns._0: uint32 block number in which the transaction began its timelock period

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Returns true if this contract implements the interface defined by `interfaceId`. See the corresponding https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-165#how-interfaces-are-identified[EIP section] to learn more about how these ids are created. This function call must use less than 30 000 gas.

params._baseGas: gas costs that are independent of the transaction execution
params._gasPrice: max gas price that should be used for this transaction
params._gasToken: token address (or 0 if ETH) that is used for the payment
params._nonce: nonce to use for the safe transaction
params._refundReceiver: address of the receiver of gas payment (or 0 if tx.origin)
params._safeTxGas: gas that should be used for the safe transaction

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

params._executionPeriod: number of blocks a transaction has to be executed within

params._timelockPeriod: new timelock period for the subDAO (in blocks)

checkAfterExecution(bytes32,bool).notice: A callback performed after a transaction is executed on the Safe. This is a required function of the `BaseGuard` and `IGuard` interfaces that we do not make use of.

checkTransaction(address,uint256,bytes,u.notice: Called by the Safe to check if the transaction is able to be executed and reverts if the guard conditions are not met.

childGnosisSafe().notice: Reference to the Safe that can be frozen.

freezeVoting().notice: Reference to the [IBaseFreezeVoting](./interfaces/IBaseFreezeVoting.md) implementation that determines whether the Safe is frozen.

getTransactionTimelockedBlock(bytes32).notice: Gets the block number that the given transaction was timelocked at.

setUp(bytes).notice: Initialize function, will be triggered when a new instance is deployed.

timelockTransaction(address,uint256,byte.notice: Allows the caller to begin the `timelock` of a transaction. Timelock is the period during which a proposed transaction must wait before being executed, after it has passed.  This period is intended to allow the parent DAO sufficient time to potentially freeze the DAO, if they should vote to do so. The parameters for doing so are identical to [ISafe's](./ISafe.md) `execTransaction` function.

updateExecutionPeriod(uint32).notice: Updates the execution period. Execution period is the time period during which a subDAO's passed Proposals must be executed, otherwise they will be expired. This period begins immediately after the timelock period has ended.
